- There is nothing wrong with the workout itself. The variety is good and I can replicated it at home.
- The intensity of his encouragements is fine. Some people need that extra "oomf!" factor to help with motivation.But what seems to be less appealing, but the combination of poor sound (maybe he had to compensate) and a tendency to "over-encourage" with clich√© sentences such as "You can do it, you are beautiful". It seems un-natural and distracting.

Compared to the other Popsugar videos, it looks "homemande". With a cleaner sound, maybe some better video editing, and more strategic motivating comments, it would be a great video workout.
